    <note>Wang(2) Xin(4) [28766] There were several judicious guesses involved in piecing together this probable lineage. Xin(4) married Zuo(1) Shi [28767], an Anyang county resident. Hu Zhiyu [28603] was Xin(4)'s son-in-law. Wang(2) Yun(5) [28617] identifies Xin, in a beiyin, as a Nanyan (南燕) person, which is the ancient name for Yidu Xian. Wang(2) Bowen(3) [28769], father of Hu(1) Zhiyu's son-in-law, Wang(2) Xixian [28770], is identified as a Donglu (東魯) or Shandong resident who moved to Zhangde Fu. There are either a strange combination of coincidences or Xin was Bowen's father.</note>
